parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to the non-deployment of airbags in the event of a crash, resulting in serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Airbag warning light illuminates
airbags fail to deploy in a crash
seatbelt sensor malfunction
corrosion in the airbag wiring harness.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt buckle can cause the airbag system to malfunction, leading to the non-deployment of airbags in the event of a crash, resulting in serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Airbag warning light illuminates
seatbelt buckle malfunction
corrosion in the seatbelt buckle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vehicle fire can cause extensive property damage and potentially result in serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Vehicle catches fire while parked or in operation.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the sun visor can cause it to fall down while driving, obstructing the driver's view and creating a safety hazard.
symptoms: The sun visor falls down or breaks off
obstructing the driver's view
making it difficult to drive safely
and causing a distraction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the EPS system can cause the steering wheel to become stiff or difficult to turn, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The EPS light on the dashboard illuminates
the steering wheel becomes stiff or difficult to turn
the vehicle pulls to one side
and the power steering fails intermittently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering column can cause the steering wheel to become loose or detached, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels loose or detached
the steering column makes a clicking or grinding noise
and the vehicle pulls to one side.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The noise and vibration in the steering system can be a precursor to more serious problems, such as EPS failure or steering column failure, and can cause driver distraction and loss of control.
symptoms: The steering wheel makes a noise or vibration when turning
the steering column makes a clicking or grinding noise
and the vehicle pulls to one side.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical fires can cause damage to the vehicle and potentially harm the occupants.
symptoms: The vehicle catches fire
often when parked or turned off
with no warning signs.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can increase the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The airbag light comes on
and the airbags may not deploy in an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake lights can increase the risk of accidents, as other drivers may not be aware of the vehicle's intentions.
symptoms: The brake lights do not function or are intermittent.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inaccuracy of the speedometer can lead to unsafe driving practices, as drivers may not be aware of their actual speed.
symptoms: The speedometer displays incorrect readings
often 5-7 mph higher or lower than actual speed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition system can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to safety risks.
symptoms: The key gets stuck in the ignition
or the vehicle will not start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the sun visor can cause distraction while driving, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The sun visor becomes disconnected and cannot be reattached.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can increase the risk of accidents, as the vehicle may not be able to stop in time.
symptoms: The brake lights do not function
or the brake pedal feels soft or spongy.
